00:19:01,461 --> 00:19:02,337
Well…

264
00:19:03,129 --> 00:19:04,172
it was fun.

265
00:19:05,215 --> 00:19:06,049
Right.

266
00:19:06,841 --> 00:19:08,259
It's fun to be with you, Na-bi.

267
00:19:11,262 --> 00:19:12,347
<i>This guy…</i>

268
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,892
<i>is bad for my heart.</i>

269
00:19:15,975 --> 00:19:17,435
Okay.

270
00:19:19,688 --> 00:19:20,689
Easy.

271
00:19:20,772 --> 00:19:21,815
Easy.

272
00:19:29,781 --> 00:19:30,657
YU JEONG-RAN

273
00:19:34,828 --> 00:19:35,787
Yes, Mom.

274
00:19:35,870 --> 00:19:39,249
<i>Na-bi.
Your aunt made your favorite side dish.</i>

275
00:19:39,332 --> 00:19:41,543
-<i>Should I ask her to send it to you?</i>
-No…

276
00:19:41,626 --> 00:19:43,920
I still have a lot left over
from last time.

277
00:19:44,003 --> 00:19:47,549
<i>Just throw away the leftovers
and eat the new ones she sends.</i>

278
00:19:47,632 --> 00:19:50,009
You always tell me to throw away stuff.

279
00:19:50,093 --> 00:19:51,010
I'm hanging up now.

280
00:19:51,094 --> 00:19:53,012
<i>Why are you in such a mood?</i>

281
00:19:53,096 --> 00:19:55,765
<i>I want my precious daughter
to have new and good stuff.</i>

282
00:19:55,849 --> 00:19:57,100
Anyway, it's fine.

283
00:19:58,685 --> 00:20:00,186
<i>When are you coming home?</i>

284
00:20:01,104 --> 00:20:05,024
<i>It's only an hour away by subway
but you never come home.</i>

285
00:20:06,109 --> 00:20:07,777
Because he's there…

286
00:20:11,448 --> 00:20:13,992
I just have a lot of assignments
these days.

287
00:20:14,659 --> 00:20:15,702
How is Ttoli?

288
00:20:16,411 --> 00:20:19,831
<i>Ttoli is always whimpering
because she misses you.</i>

289
00:20:20,457 --> 00:20:23,126
<i>Bring your boyfriend.
I'll treat you to delicious food.</i>

290
00:20:23,209 --> 00:20:24,294
There's no boyfriend.

291
00:20:25,128 --> 00:20:27,630
<i>What? Did you break up?</i>

292
00:20:30,091 --> 00:20:31,259
<i>Na-bi.</i>

293
00:20:35,054 --> 00:20:37,474
Mom, I need to hang up.

294
00:20:55,492 --> 00:20:56,701
What?

295
00:21:25,855 --> 00:21:27,816
Why were you named after a butterfly?

296
00:21:29,776 --> 00:21:33,446
So my life could be sweet like honey.
My mom and aunt named me.

297
00:21:37,492 --> 00:21:38,576
I'm just kidding.

298
00:21:41,287 --> 00:21:43,248
Do you know Nathaniel Hawthorne?

299
00:21:44,582 --> 00:21:46,626
He's my aunt's favorite author,

300
00:21:47,544 --> 00:21:49,128
and he said this.

301
00:21:49,712 --> 00:21:51,631
It's a bit cringey to quote it.

302
00:21:54,801 --> 00:21:56,553
"Happiness is like a butterfly which,

303
00:21:58,346 --> 00:22:01,015
when pursued, is always beyond our grasp,

304
00:22:01,099 --> 00:22:05,311
but, if you will sit down quietly,
may alight upon you."

305
00:22:10,233 --> 00:22:11,901
That's the back story.

306
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:15,822
It's nothing special.

307
00:22:15,905 --> 00:22:16,739
No…

308
00:22:18,032 --> 00:22:18,992
I love it.

309
00:22:38,928 --> 00:22:40,179
Is that a butterfly…

310
00:22:41,180 --> 00:22:42,265
on your neck?

311
00:22:42,348 --> 00:22:43,349
Yes.

312
00:22:46,477 --> 00:22:47,687
I like…

313
00:22:50,523 --> 00:22:51,482
butterflies.

314
00:23:03,536 --> 00:23:04,579
All done.

315
00:23:11,586 --> 00:23:12,837
It's cute.

316
00:23:14,756 --> 00:23:16,674
Is this really your wish?

317
00:23:17,884 --> 00:23:19,719
That was pretty simple.

318
00:23:22,805 --> 00:23:23,681
Then should I…

319
00:23:26,142 --> 00:23:27,226
make another wish?

320
00:23:44,202 --> 00:23:45,495
This is silly.

321
00:23:46,579 --> 00:23:47,413
What do you mean?

322
00:23:49,040 --> 00:23:49,957
It's nothing.

323
00:24:05,807 --> 00:24:07,392
The moon is pretty today.

324
00:24:16,359 --> 00:24:17,443
Do you want one?

325
00:24:20,655 --> 00:24:21,698
It's my last one.

326
00:24:22,281 --> 00:24:23,533
Well…

327
00:24:23,616 --> 00:24:25,410
I don't smoke.

328
00:24:28,246 --> 00:24:29,664
Excuse me.

329
00:24:29,747 --> 00:24:31,290
Can I borrow a cigarette?

330
00:24:33,835 --> 00:24:35,044
Gosh.

331
00:24:35,128 --> 00:24:37,171
I'm sobering up.

332
00:24:38,047 --> 00:24:41,384
Hey, can I borrow a cigarette?

333
00:24:42,260 --> 00:24:46,931
If we run into each other next time,
I promise to return the favor.

334
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:50,727
I do have one, but…

335
00:25:06,033 --> 00:25:08,619
What the hell?

336
00:25:30,600 --> 00:25:31,684
What?

337
00:25:33,436 --> 00:25:34,479
Why are you smiling?

338
00:25:52,830 --> 00:25:53,873
Are you okay?

339
00:25:57,001 --> 00:25:58,211
Yes.

340
00:25:58,795 --> 00:26:00,046
I'm fine.

341
00:26:21,526 --> 00:26:23,236
Do you want to go see butterflies?

342
00:26:24,320 --> 00:26:26,322
Where would we see them?

343
00:26:28,491 --> 00:26:29,575
At my place.

344
00:26:38,292 --> 00:26:40,127
Let me go to the bathroom for a minute.

345
00:26:51,681 --> 00:26:52,640
What are you doing?

346
00:26:54,433 --> 00:26:55,768
I miss you too.

347
00:26:57,228 --> 00:26:58,479
Are you going to sleep?

348
00:27:03,234 --> 00:27:04,151
Yes.

349
00:27:07,613 --> 00:27:09,448
<i>What? So you just left?</i>

350
00:27:10,032 --> 00:27:11,784
Did you contact him after that?

351
00:27:11,868 --> 00:27:13,119
Of course not.

352
00:27:13,786 --> 00:27:16,914
I told him about where my name came from,
but I don't even know his name.

353
00:27:16,998 --> 00:27:19,333
You mustered up your courage, though.
Too bad.

354
00:27:22,461 --> 00:27:23,546
What's that?

355
00:27:25,298 --> 00:27:26,549
Oh, this?

356
00:27:26,632 --> 00:27:27,717
Well…

357
00:27:28,342 --> 00:27:29,594
It's nothing.

358
00:27:29,677 --> 00:27:30,803
It's love.

359
00:27:31,762 --> 00:27:34,348
It's nothing like that.

360
00:27:34,432 --> 00:27:36,017
-Then what is it?
-Lust?

361
00:27:36,100 --> 00:27:37,894
I don't know. It's just…

362
00:27:39,312 --> 00:27:40,479
It was fun.

363
00:27:40,563 --> 00:27:45,192
It's hard to find someone
you feel an instant connection with.

364
00:27:45,276 --> 00:27:47,445
Never mind that.
You said he has a girlfriend.

365
00:27:48,154 --> 00:27:50,740
You should never hang out with cheaters.

366
00:27:52,909 --> 00:27:55,578
Oh, right.
I have to post the part-time job ad.

367
00:27:55,661 --> 00:27:57,371
Or should I ask some of the kids?

368
00:27:57,455 --> 00:27:58,664
All right.

369
00:27:59,582 --> 00:28:01,000
How about Jae-eon?

370
00:28:01,083 --> 00:28:03,336
I'm not sure. Would he do it?

371
00:28:03,419 --> 00:28:06,589
I'll try to convince him.

372
00:28:10,217 --> 00:28:11,260
Hello.

373
00:28:11,344 --> 00:28:13,387
Oh, do, re, mi, fa, sol. Sol is here.

374
00:28:15,389 --> 00:28:17,058
I have a meeting with the professor.

375
00:28:17,141 --> 00:28:19,185
Right. Go inside with Na-bi.

376
00:28:22,897 --> 00:28:25,566
-Together?
-Together?

377
00:28:25,650 --> 00:28:28,611
It's okay. Sol can have the meeting first.

378
00:28:28,694 --> 00:28:30,363
It'll be a waste of time.

379
00:28:30,446 --> 00:28:32,198
It's about
the exchange student program, right?

380
00:28:32,949 --> 00:28:36,369
The professor's nagging will get longer
if it's one-on-one.

381
00:28:36,452 --> 00:28:37,495
Right.

382
00:28:38,162 --> 00:28:39,497
Right.

383
00:28:40,498 --> 00:28:41,332
Bye, then.

384
00:28:41,415 --> 00:28:42,375
Bye.

385
00:28:45,419 --> 00:28:47,046
You're really clueless, aren't you?

386
00:28:47,129 --> 00:28:48,756
What do you mean?

387
00:28:48,839 --> 00:28:52,718
Na-bi was feeling uncomfortable since
she didn't want to be compared to Sol.

388
00:28:52,802 --> 00:28:54,136
Is that so?

389
00:28:55,471 --> 00:28:57,306
You only picked hard places to get in.

390
00:28:58,516 --> 00:29:01,686
Na-bi, it'll be difficult to get
accepted to any of these schools.

391
00:29:01,769 --> 00:29:02,895
You know that, right?

392
00:29:05,815 --> 00:29:06,649
Yes.

393
00:29:06,732 --> 00:29:07,984
I'm not saying you're bad.

394
00:29:08,067 --> 00:29:09,652
You're doing well,

395
00:29:10,361 --> 00:29:12,405
but there are only
a limited number of spots.

396
00:29:13,281 --> 00:29:15,283
You have to raise your GPA.

397
00:29:15,366 --> 00:29:16,826
Work harder, okay?

398
00:29:17,743 --> 00:29:19,078
Yes, ma'am.

399
00:29:19,161 --> 00:29:22,540
And going abroad isn't always
the best answer.

400
00:29:22,623 --> 00:29:24,834
Staying in Korea could be a better option.

401
00:29:24,917 --> 00:29:27,920
Domestic graduate schools
are pretty good too.

402
00:29:28,004 --> 00:29:30,840
There's no place like Korea for Koreans,

403
00:29:30,923 --> 00:29:31,966
don't you think?

404
00:29:33,009 --> 00:29:35,177
Right.

405
00:29:35,261 --> 00:29:37,596
Let's talk again next time, then.

406
00:29:38,597 --> 00:29:40,057
What about you, Sol?

407
00:29:40,141 --> 00:29:42,059
You didn't submit your list?

408
00:29:42,143 --> 00:29:44,270
No, not yet.

409
00:29:44,353 --> 00:29:46,897
You could start next semester.
What are you waiting for?

410
00:29:46,981 --> 00:29:48,941
Is there something going on?

411
00:29:51,110 --> 00:29:52,445
No.

412
00:29:53,321 --> 00:29:55,406
I'll make my decision soon, ma'am.

413
00:29:56,449 --> 00:29:59,243
All right.
I'd prefer it if you made it quick.

414
00:29:59,910 --> 00:30:01,120
It's a waste of time.

415
00:30:01,662 --> 00:30:03,873
You might think it won't be any different.

416
00:30:03,956 --> 00:30:07,126
But there are things you can learn
from the world out there.

417
00:30:08,169 --> 00:30:09,545
This is a great list.

418
00:30:10,212 --> 00:30:13,299
Take a look at this,
and make your decision.

419
00:30:15,217 --> 00:30:16,927
LIST OF PROSPECTIVE UNIVERSITIES

420
00:30:17,011 --> 00:30:17,970
Yes, ma'am.

421
00:30:19,597 --> 00:30:22,975
Why do you two look so gloomy?

422
00:30:23,059 --> 00:30:25,186
You should be shining at that age.

423
00:30:25,269 --> 00:30:26,896
Don't stay holed up in the studio.

424
00:30:26,979 --> 00:30:29,357
You should make your life eventful

425
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:32,610
to get inspiration for your work.
Got that?

426
00:30:33,778 --> 00:30:34,653
Yes.

427
00:30:35,821 --> 00:30:36,864
Yes.

428
00:30:41,202 --> 00:30:44,038
I think she said the word "inspiration"
over 100 times.

429
00:30:46,874 --> 00:30:48,334
Just take it.

430
00:30:48,417 --> 00:30:50,961
I was about to give you the file
if you needed it anyway.

431
00:30:52,004 --> 00:30:53,381
Thanks. It'll be helpful.

432
00:30:54,340 --> 00:30:56,509
It was so embarrassing, though.

433
00:30:57,176 --> 00:30:58,135
What was?

434
00:30:58,719 --> 00:31:02,056
I listed up all the great universities
without thinking about my grades.

435
00:31:02,765 --> 00:31:05,434
I'm jealous, Sol.
You can go pretty much anywhere.

436
00:31:07,895 --> 00:31:10,606
It might not be the best idea
to go abroad.

437
00:31:12,483 --> 00:31:15,236
Honestly, it kind of feels like
I'm just trying to run away.

438
00:31:16,028 --> 00:31:17,279
Were you thinking that too?

439
00:31:17,363 --> 00:31:19,115
Yun Sol!

440
00:31:22,118 --> 00:31:23,661
Oh, you were with Na-bi.

441
00:31:23,744 --> 00:31:26,330
What did the professor say?
Why did she call you two?

442
00:31:26,414 --> 00:31:27,623
It was for the exchange--

443
00:31:27,706 --> 00:31:30,084
Just talking about assignment ideas.

444
00:31:30,167 --> 00:31:31,293
Assignment ideas?

445
00:31:31,377 --> 00:31:34,880
Why did she leave me out?
This is favoritism.

446
00:31:34,964 --> 00:31:36,757
She just gave us a bit of advice.

447
00:31:37,633 --> 00:31:38,717
We'll be off.

448
00:31:39,385 --> 00:31:41,220
Oh, okay. Bye.

449
00:31:41,303 --> 00:31:42,263
Bye, Na-bi.

450
00:31:43,764 --> 00:31:46,892
I'm the one who's out of ideas.

451
00:31:56,318 --> 00:31:57,736
Why are you dressed so nicely?

452
00:31:57,820 --> 00:32:00,072
Do I look nice? That's a relief.

453
00:32:00,781 --> 00:32:02,867
Is it because we're gathering today?

454
00:32:02,950 --> 00:32:04,160
Well…

455
00:32:04,243 --> 00:32:06,704
my blind date was supposed to be tomorrow,

456
00:32:06,787 --> 00:32:09,415
but he said something urgent came up

457
00:32:09,498 --> 00:32:11,208
and asked if we could meet today.

458
00:32:11,292 --> 00:32:13,169
Otherwise, it'll be a while later.

459
00:32:13,252 --> 00:32:16,130
You know how you shouldn't
put off a blind date for too long.

460
00:32:16,213 --> 00:32:18,132
So I just agreed to meet him today.

461
00:32:18,215 --> 00:32:20,885
What? Then what about our gathering today?

462
00:32:20,968 --> 00:32:22,386
Tell the others for me.

463
00:32:22,470 --> 00:32:25,431
Hey, I didn't want to go.
You're the one who made a fuss.

464
00:32:25,514 --> 00:32:27,683
I know. I'm really sorry.

465
00:32:27,766 --> 00:32:29,768
But if you don't go either,

466
00:32:29,852 --> 00:32:33,189
everyone will curse me to death. Please?

467
00:32:33,272 --> 00:32:34,857
-Sol, please.
-Gosh.

468
00:32:34,940 --> 00:32:36,150
All right.

469
00:32:36,233 --> 00:32:37,067
I love you!

470
00:32:37,151 --> 00:32:40,237
If things go well with my date,
I'll set you up with someone too.

471
00:32:40,321 --> 00:32:41,280
There's no need.

472
00:32:41,363 --> 00:32:42,698
Oh, come on.

473
00:33:17,525 --> 00:33:19,485
-Hi. What brings you here?
-Hello.

474
00:33:19,568 --> 00:33:21,320
-Hello.
-Hello.

475
00:33:22,238 --> 00:33:24,031
-Keep working.
-Okay.

476
00:33:27,159 --> 00:33:28,661
I already chiseled it off.

477
00:34:11,870 --> 00:34:13,831
<i>You have to raise your GPA.</i>

478
00:34:26,302 --> 00:34:29,138
So you're really going to stay up working?

479
00:34:29,680 --> 00:34:30,556
Yes.

480
00:34:31,599 --> 00:34:33,517
Or I might not be able to finish on time.

481
00:34:33,601 --> 00:34:34,977
My progress is slow.

482
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:37,438
Alcohol is the best when you're stuck.

483
00:34:37,980 --> 00:34:39,648
I'm going to go drink with the kids.

484
00:34:41,066 --> 00:34:42,818
You don't know any of our juniors.

485
00:34:42,901 --> 00:34:45,112
Don't you need an assistant
for the exhibit?

486
00:34:45,863 --> 00:34:50,367
At this rate, you'll be the first one
in our department to do everything alone.

487
00:34:55,164 --> 00:34:57,124
Gosh. Never mind.

488
00:34:57,708 --> 00:34:59,376
There's no way
you'll get a new boyfriend like that.

489
00:34:59,460 --> 00:35:00,628
Bye.

490
00:35:03,547 --> 00:35:05,132
Call me if you change your mind.

491
00:35:06,258 --> 00:35:07,259
Okay.

492
00:35:08,552 --> 00:35:09,845
Have fun!

493
00:35:09,928 --> 00:35:11,013
I will!

494
00:35:56,975 --> 00:35:58,686
That will be 14,000 won.

495
00:35:58,769 --> 00:35:59,770
Here.

496
00:36:07,778 --> 00:36:08,821
<i>It's him.</i>

497
00:36:10,322 --> 00:36:11,281
Hang on.

498
00:36:24,086 --> 00:36:25,504
<i>The library, and now this.</i>

499
00:36:27,172 --> 00:36:28,882
<i>I must be losing my mind.</i>

500
00:36:34,555 --> 00:36:35,764
<i>You're really not coming?</i>

501
00:36:42,938 --> 00:36:44,648
Bit-na, where's the location?

502
00:37:04,460 --> 00:37:05,669
We meet again.

503
00:37:09,423 --> 00:37:12,551
What are you doing here?

504
00:37:16,805 --> 00:37:17,639
Hey, you're here.

505
00:37:17,723 --> 00:37:20,267
-Hi. I'm heading in first.
-Okay.

506
00:37:26,190 --> 00:37:27,107
He's the junior…

507
00:37:28,192 --> 00:37:29,735
who was hoping to drink with you.

508
00:37:33,697 --> 00:37:34,823
I see.

509
00:37:35,616 --> 00:37:37,367
Look! You're screwed.

510
00:37:40,204 --> 00:37:42,581
Gosh, this place is flooded with seniors.

511
00:37:43,165 --> 00:37:44,041
Seniors!

512
00:37:44,124 --> 00:37:46,585
Are you sick of your seniors?

513
00:37:46,668 --> 00:37:47,628
Not at all!

514
00:37:50,380 --> 00:37:51,924
But we have a newbie now.

515
00:37:53,342 --> 00:37:55,803
She made a rare appearance,
so be nice to her.

516
00:37:58,597 --> 00:38:01,099
This is Yu Na-bi,
and this is Park Jae-eon.

517
00:38:02,768 --> 00:38:03,894
<i>Park Jae-eon…</i>

518
00:38:04,478 --> 00:38:05,312
Oh, okay.

519
00:38:05,395 --> 00:38:08,398
<i>His name was Park Jae-eon.</i>

520
00:38:10,275 --> 00:38:11,568
What's with the face?

521
00:38:13,862 --> 00:38:14,947
Do you know each other?

522
00:38:17,032 --> 00:38:18,158
No.

523
00:38:18,659 --> 00:38:21,495
-It's our first time seeing each other.
-It's your first time?

524
00:38:21,578 --> 00:38:22,996
They took turns taking a leave.

525
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:26,458
And Na-bi barely attends school events.

526
00:38:26,542 --> 00:38:30,128
-That's right. She never shows up.
-But you come to all of them.

527
00:38:30,212 --> 00:38:31,630
Hi.

528
00:38:36,885 --> 00:38:38,470
Oh. Hi.

529
00:38:38,554 --> 00:38:41,056
I just got butterflies in my stomach!

530
00:38:41,139 --> 00:38:42,599
"Oh. Hi."

