00:55:59,969 --> 00:56:01,887
-Why were you startled?
-Mr. An, please.

801
00:56:01,971 --> 00:56:03,723
I'm more startled at your piece.

802
00:56:03,806 --> 00:56:05,057
Why is there no progress?

803
00:56:05,141 --> 00:56:07,351
-I can't seem to get the color right.
-Well, I…

804
00:56:07,435 --> 00:56:09,020
I'm almost done.

805
00:56:09,103 --> 00:56:11,731
This shouldn't be "almost done." Okay?

806
00:56:13,983 --> 00:56:14,984
I'll work late today.

807
00:56:15,067 --> 00:56:16,527
Working late isn't going to…

808
00:56:20,865 --> 00:56:22,908
-Let's talk later.
-Yes, ma'am.

809
00:56:34,295 --> 00:56:35,630
-Hey, Bit-na.
-What?

810
00:56:35,713 --> 00:56:37,673
Did everyone send the money last night?

811
00:56:37,757 --> 00:56:39,383
What? Yes, everyone sent it.

812
00:56:39,467 --> 00:56:40,468
Why?

813
00:56:40,551 --> 00:56:41,927
I was just curious.

814
00:56:42,011 --> 00:56:43,220
They all sent it.

815
00:56:47,808 --> 00:56:49,810
Jae-eon gave it to me in cash right away.

816
00:56:52,396 --> 00:56:53,230
Oh.

817
00:56:56,525 --> 00:56:57,735
Keep going.

818
00:56:59,236 --> 00:57:00,237
Focus, all right?

819
00:57:00,321 --> 00:57:01,572
I am.

820
00:57:07,620 --> 00:57:10,373
I'm so full.
My stomach's going to explode.

821
00:57:10,456 --> 00:57:11,707
Mine first.

822
00:57:11,791 --> 00:57:12,959
I can't breathe.

823
00:57:13,626 --> 00:57:15,169
But I can still eat dessert.

824
00:57:15,252 --> 00:57:16,796
I can totally eat cake.

825
00:57:16,879 --> 00:57:17,880
I can eat cake too!

826
00:57:17,964 --> 00:57:19,966
I can eat it with coffee!

827
00:57:21,217 --> 00:57:22,802
We have some time left. Shall we?

828
00:57:22,885 --> 00:57:25,763
-Sure, you little foodie.
-You guys are coming too, right?

829
00:57:25,846 --> 00:57:26,681
Of course.

830
00:57:27,223 --> 00:57:30,142
Your stomachs are really going to explode.

831
00:57:30,226 --> 00:57:33,062
He always picks a fight
when he's going to join us anyway.

832
00:57:33,145 --> 00:57:33,980
Tell me about it.

833
00:57:34,063 --> 00:57:34,981
Oh, no.

834
00:57:35,064 --> 00:57:36,649
Where are my Bluetooth earphones?

835
00:57:39,276 --> 00:57:40,903
I left them at the outdoor studio.

836
00:57:41,404 --> 00:57:43,197
Someone's going to steal them for sure.

837
00:57:43,698 --> 00:57:47,535
There are security cameras everywhere.
Nobody will take them.

838
00:57:47,618 --> 00:57:48,786
Right?

839
00:57:48,869 --> 00:57:50,329
It's so far away.

840
00:57:50,413 --> 00:57:52,456
-I'll just ask in our chat room.
-Wait. I'll get them.

841
00:57:53,124 --> 00:57:53,958
Really?

842
00:57:54,041 --> 00:57:55,292
Yes.

843
00:57:55,376 --> 00:57:57,420
It's fine. You don't need to.

844
00:57:57,503 --> 00:58:00,006
No, I was about to go back anyway.

845
00:58:00,089 --> 00:58:02,299
I'll get them and put them in your locker.

846
00:58:02,383 --> 00:58:03,592
Send me your passcode.

847
00:58:03,676 --> 00:58:05,052
I'm so touched.

848
00:58:05,136 --> 00:58:06,012
Thank you.

849
00:58:06,095 --> 00:58:07,388
It's nothing.

850
00:58:08,639 --> 00:58:09,932
She's so kind.

851
00:58:11,934 --> 00:58:12,893
What should I do?

852
00:58:13,561 --> 00:58:16,022
I'm so popular.

853
00:58:16,105 --> 00:58:18,607
Dream on. She'd never fall for you.

854
00:58:19,108 --> 00:58:22,194
I was just saying!
Why would she do that for me?

855
00:58:22,278 --> 00:58:24,905
She was going to head back anyway.

856
00:58:24,989 --> 00:58:26,657
Never mind. Let's go have some cake.

857
00:58:26,741 --> 00:58:28,034
Yes!

858
00:58:36,417 --> 00:58:38,961
What's this? Is it a bat?

859
00:58:40,087 --> 00:58:42,048
A bat? It's a butterfly.

860
00:58:43,424 --> 00:58:46,385
This piece sure feels different
from all the other ones.

861
00:58:46,469 --> 00:58:47,720
Right.

862
00:58:47,803 --> 00:58:51,265
I don't even see him often at the studio.
When did he do all this?

863
00:58:51,849 --> 00:58:53,142
He must be a genius.

864
00:58:53,225 --> 00:58:55,978
Jae-eon won almost
all the competitions last year.

865
00:58:56,479 --> 00:58:59,065
And he's even handsome.
Life's so unfair, isn't it?

866
00:59:00,483 --> 00:59:01,901
So that was Jae-eon's.

867
00:59:02,526 --> 00:59:04,153
But where did Jae-eon…

868
00:59:04,236 --> 00:59:05,696
Oh. Hi, Na-bi.

869
00:59:06,489 --> 00:59:07,406
Hi.

870
00:59:07,490 --> 00:59:08,741
What brings you here?

871
00:59:09,366 --> 00:59:10,701
Well…

872
00:59:10,785 --> 00:59:13,329
Jin-su said he left something behind.

873
00:59:13,412 --> 00:59:15,414
Did you see Bluetooth earphones
lying around?

874
00:59:15,498 --> 00:59:16,749
-No.
-No.

875
00:59:16,832 --> 00:59:18,292
You should look around.

876
00:59:18,375 --> 00:59:19,251
Okay, I will.

877
00:59:25,466 --> 00:59:26,675
Oh, Jae-eon!

878
00:59:28,052 --> 00:59:28,886
Hey, Jae-eon.

879
00:59:28,969 --> 00:59:29,929
Hey.

880
00:59:30,012 --> 00:59:30,930
Hi, Jae-eon.

881
00:59:34,725 --> 00:59:35,810
Hi.

882
00:59:36,644 --> 00:59:37,645
Hi.

883
00:59:38,437 --> 00:59:39,438
Looking for something?

884
00:59:40,564 --> 00:59:41,482
No.

885
00:59:44,985 --> 00:59:46,654
Jae-eon, that's a butterfly, right?

886
00:59:46,737 --> 00:59:48,489
She said it looks like a bat.

887
00:59:49,240 --> 00:59:51,951
You recognized it?
Everyone thinks it's a bat.

888
00:59:52,034 --> 00:59:53,702
You must really like butterflies.

889
00:59:53,786 --> 00:59:56,580
-Your last piece was one too.
-Do you want to see my butterflies?

890
00:59:56,664 --> 00:59:57,581
Yes. Show us.

891
00:59:57,665 --> 00:59:58,791
Yes, please.

892
01:00:02,253 --> 01:00:03,838
They're so pretty.

893
01:00:05,131 --> 01:00:08,509
Is that what your tattoo is about?
Like people get tattoos of their pets?

894
01:00:13,764 --> 01:00:15,015
Do they have names?

895
01:00:16,058 --> 01:00:17,685
No, I just call them butterflies.

896
01:00:20,688 --> 01:00:21,605
"Butterfly."

897
01:00:24,567 --> 01:00:25,734
It's a pretty name.

898
01:00:45,713 --> 01:00:46,547
I like…

899
01:00:49,049 --> 01:00:50,176
butterflies.

900
01:00:51,510 --> 01:00:52,469
"Butterfly."

901
01:00:53,095 --> 01:00:54,054
It's a pretty name.

902
01:00:54,680 --> 01:00:56,682
<i>Jae-eon keeps making me think</i>

903
01:00:56,765 --> 01:00:59,268
<i>the way my annoying ex did.</i>

904
01:00:59,351 --> 01:01:02,938
It's so stupid to read too much into
meaningless stuff.

905
01:01:06,025 --> 01:01:08,527
You idiot.

906
01:01:09,236 --> 01:01:10,529
Who's an idiot?

907
01:01:14,241 --> 01:01:15,201
Don't look.

908
01:01:16,118 --> 01:01:18,996
Is this seaweed?

909
01:01:21,373 --> 01:01:25,461
Why did you have to appear out of nowhere
and surprise me like that?

910
01:01:25,544 --> 01:01:27,129
You're just insensitive.

911
01:01:27,671 --> 01:01:30,716
You left without a word.
I thought you had something to say.

912
01:01:33,719 --> 01:01:35,346
No, I didn't have anything…

913
01:01:36,263 --> 01:01:38,766
I was just looking
for my friend's belongings.

914
01:01:42,478 --> 01:01:44,521
<i>You know how popular you are, right?</i>

915
01:01:46,607 --> 01:01:49,401
<i>That's why you have that look
and talk that way.</i>

916
01:01:53,822 --> 01:01:54,865
What?

917
01:01:56,033 --> 01:01:57,493
There's the seaweed.

918
01:01:58,202 --> 01:01:59,662
-Come here.
-Sorry.

919
01:01:59,745 --> 01:02:01,747
I'm sorry! Stop it.

920
01:02:01,830 --> 01:02:03,916
-Wipe it off.
-Okay, I will.

921
01:02:03,999 --> 01:02:05,292
I'll wipe it off for you.

922
01:02:10,339 --> 01:02:12,758
-Sorry! Okay, I'll really wipe it off.
-Hang on.

923
01:02:12,841 --> 01:02:14,343
-You'd better.
-What?

924
01:02:14,426 --> 01:02:16,220
-Come on, wipe it off.
-When did they get so close?

925
01:02:16,303 --> 01:02:18,639
They look pretty good together. Hey!

926
01:02:18,722 --> 01:02:19,974
What?

927
01:02:20,057 --> 01:02:21,141
Let's just go.

928
01:02:21,225 --> 01:02:22,518
-Why?
-Come on. Let's go.

929
01:03:51,940 --> 01:03:55,361
Why do my shoulders hurt so much?
I wish they had high bars at school.

930
01:04:02,868 --> 01:04:03,702
Relax.

931
01:04:05,329 --> 01:04:07,289
Your back was hunched
when you were working.

932
01:04:07,373 --> 01:04:10,125
Hey, let go. Wait.

933
01:04:10,209 --> 01:04:12,127
Wait. Stop.

934
01:04:24,431 --> 01:04:26,308
I almost fell down.

935
01:04:37,861 --> 01:04:40,280
Bit-na says
you practically live in the studio.

936
01:04:40,864 --> 01:04:42,699
Not really.

937
01:04:43,617 --> 01:04:45,369
I like working at night,

938
01:04:45,452 --> 01:04:47,746
so I often stay late. What about you?

939
01:04:48,247 --> 01:04:49,665
I might try it more often.

940
01:04:50,249 --> 01:04:51,166
It was fun.

941
01:04:52,709 --> 01:04:54,670
<i>As we talk,</i>

942
01:04:54,753 --> 01:04:56,672
<i>I can see different sides of Jae-eon.</i>

943
01:04:59,049 --> 01:05:00,300
I envy you.

944
01:05:01,301 --> 01:05:03,846
It used to be fun for me a long time ago.

945
01:05:05,180 --> 01:05:06,557
It's not fun anymore?

946
01:05:07,224 --> 01:05:09,977
There's a lot to think about now.

947
01:05:11,562 --> 01:05:13,605
And I'm not sure what to do.

948
01:05:13,689 --> 01:05:15,357
You wanted to be an exchange student.

949
01:05:16,358 --> 01:05:17,693
It seems like a good goal.

950
01:05:18,277 --> 01:05:19,570
It's nothing.

951
01:05:21,530 --> 01:05:24,575
It sounds special,
but lots of students do it.

952
01:05:28,579 --> 01:05:29,580
And honestly…

953
01:05:33,125 --> 01:05:35,210
I just want to go somewhere far away.

954
01:05:36,795 --> 01:05:37,629
Why?

955
01:05:39,131 --> 01:05:41,049
Because of my mom and…

956
01:05:42,509 --> 01:05:44,303
Let's stop talking about this.

957
01:05:44,887 --> 01:05:45,804
It's boring.

958
01:05:47,598 --> 01:05:48,724
It's not boring to me.

959
01:05:50,309 --> 01:05:51,977
You're talking about your true self.

960
01:05:53,854 --> 01:05:56,273
<i>He's different from
the first impression I had of him.</i>

961
01:05:57,399 --> 01:06:00,068
<i>I wanted to believe
that only I knew this side of him.</i>

962
01:06:08,744 --> 01:06:10,370
There's the moon you like.

963
01:06:17,753 --> 01:06:18,754
It's pretty.

964
01:06:21,965 --> 01:06:23,050
It's pretty.

965
01:06:33,936 --> 01:06:34,811
Your number.

966
01:06:40,150 --> 01:06:41,693
Oh. My number?

967
01:06:45,447 --> 01:06:47,658
<i>It feels like something new
is about to begin.</i>

968
01:06:48,784 --> 01:06:50,035
<i>I'm probably not mistaken.</i>

969
01:06:55,791 --> 01:06:58,418
Yu Na-bi. I saved your number.

970
01:07:00,170 --> 01:07:02,381
<i>You know that I'm Na-bi.</i>

971
01:07:08,220 --> 01:07:09,263
Do you want one?

972
01:07:10,138 --> 01:07:11,306
No, thanks.

973
01:07:15,394 --> 01:07:16,687
Did you get it customized?

974
01:07:17,854 --> 01:07:18,689
Yes.

975
01:07:19,815 --> 01:07:20,691
Isn't it pretty?

976
01:07:22,943 --> 01:07:24,444
Another butterfly.

977
01:07:25,320 --> 01:07:26,738
Oh, show me too.

978
01:07:27,489 --> 01:07:29,825
-What?
-Your pet butterflies.

979
01:07:31,159 --> 01:07:33,245
-Oh, my butterflies?
-Yes.

980
01:07:33,912 --> 01:07:35,038
Want to go see them?

981
01:07:39,418 --> 01:07:42,629
I mean, I want to see the video

982
01:07:42,713 --> 01:07:45,132
that you showed your friends. Gosh.

983
01:08:00,272 --> 01:08:01,565
They're pretty.

984
01:08:05,152 --> 01:08:06,820
What do you like so much about them?

985
01:08:13,577 --> 01:08:17,539
They sometimes crawl up
onto my face like this.

986
01:08:18,915 --> 01:08:20,250
It feels really nice.

987
01:08:26,173 --> 01:08:27,299
It's lovely.

988
01:08:32,471 --> 01:08:33,847
That tickles.

989
01:08:38,060 --> 01:08:40,228
I want to smoke, too.

990
01:08:45,859 --> 01:08:47,361
I don't want to go back inside.

991
01:08:52,157 --> 01:08:53,116
Me neither.

992
01:08:58,455 --> 01:08:59,831
You don't smoke, though.

993
01:09:00,707 --> 01:09:02,084
Do you want to go have drinks?

994
01:09:02,167 --> 01:09:03,210
Drinks?

995
01:09:06,046 --> 01:09:07,881
Are you going to work some more? Then…

996
01:09:07,964 --> 01:09:10,008
No. Let's go.

997
01:09:10,926 --> 01:09:12,010
Just the two of us?

998
01:09:15,597 --> 01:09:17,057
Well…

999
01:09:17,140 --> 01:09:18,934
we can call our friends.

1000
01:09:19,935 --> 01:09:21,186
Should I call them?

1001
01:09:21,770 --> 01:09:22,729
Why are you laughing?

1002
01:09:22,813 --> 01:09:24,022
I don't know.

1003
01:09:25,065 --> 01:09:26,358
You make me laugh.

1004
01:09:29,152 --> 01:09:31,029
Are you that happy to drink with me?

1005
01:09:31,113 --> 01:09:32,114
I am.

1006
01:09:44,543 --> 01:09:45,377
<i>I'm sure…</i>

1007
01:09:46,878 --> 01:09:48,505
<i>that we feel the same way.</i>

1008
01:10:45,812 --> 01:10:47,147
<i>I'm using my wish.</i>

1009
01:10:47,230 --> 01:10:49,858
<i>I'm sure he does this to everyone.
I know everything.</i>

1010
01:10:49,941 --> 01:10:52,486
<i>Park Jae-eon?
He has no interest at all in dating.</i>

1011
01:10:52,569 --> 01:10:53,695
<i>So forget him.</i>

1012
01:10:54,321 --> 01:10:55,363
-<i>Hey!</i>
-<i>Are you hurt?</i>

1013
01:10:55,447 --> 01:10:57,908
<i>Jae-eon keeps making me feel excited.</i>

1014
01:10:58,492 --> 01:11:00,494
<i>Do people have to date?</i>

1015
01:11:00,577 --> 01:11:03,830
<i>Why can't two people just be close?</i>

1016
01:11:03,914 --> 01:11:05,123
<i>Can't they stand near each other?</i>

1017
01:11:05,207 --> 01:11:07,542
<i>Do they have to pretend not to notice
if there's something in their hair?</i>

1018
01:11:08,251 --> 01:11:10,879
<i>What do I want from Jae-eon?</i>

1019
01:11:10,962 --> 01:11:13,173
<i>You sometimes suddenly act cold to me.</i>

1020
01:11:13,256 --> 01:11:17,260
Bit-na and I are going to drink
at my house. Do you want to come?

1021
01:11:17,344 --> 01:11:19,554
The two people
the bottle points to have to kiss!

1022
01:11:21,556 --> 01:11:25,018
<i>Right. I should just check for myself
and forget about him.</i>

1023
01:11:27,020 --> 01:11:30,440
Subtitle translation by: Ju-young Park

